HEADWORD: Oxalyl
<hw>Ox"a*lyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oxal</ets>ic +
<ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
hydrocarbon radical (<chform>C2O2</chform>) regarded as a residue of
oxalic acid and occurring in derivatives of it.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>An old name for <altname>carbonyl</altname>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>An old name for <altname>carboxyl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

